What is Exudate Absorbent Dressings?
These dressings incorporate a range of absorbent materials-such as foam, hydrogel, alginate, and emerging super‑absorbent polymers-to capture excess exudate while maintaining a balanced moisture level that supports granulation tissue formation. Their designs often include features like silicone border layers to minimise trauma at removal, antimicrobial additives to curb infection, and visual indicators that signal saturation levels to clinicians. The combination of these attributes makes them indispensable across acute, chronic and postoperative wound management pathways.
